  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Facebook does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profile. Facebook prioritizes user privacy, and this includes not disclosing data about who visits your profile.\n\nIf you come across third-party applications or services that claim to show you who has viewed your profile, be cautious. These may not be legitimate and can compromise your privacy or security. It's best to avoid such apps.\n\nThe only statistics about engagement you can find are related to your posts and interactions on Facebook, such as likes, comments, and shares. For personal profiles, this means you can see who reacted to or commented on your posts, but not who viewed your profile overall. \n\nAlways ensure that you're aware of privacy settings and who can see your content on your profile by checking your privacy settings in the Facebook app or website.",
